cle"],[990,"Limit"],[691,"link an existing run: `POST /api/work-items/{id}/link-run` with `{ \"runId\": \"run_...\" }` (relinking moves the run and leaves an unlink event on the old ticket);"],[172,"Linked run becomes"],[656,"Linked runs and attention"],[693,"Linked runs bring their approvals and artifacts with them: the ticket detail aggregates both across all linked runs."],[171,"Linked runs keep the board honest without an operator shepherding every card. The mapping is deliberately conservative:"],[970,"List / inspect drafts with their latest preflight report"],[927,"List a run's artifacts; download bytes"],[688,"List and detail payloads carry a linked-run rollup — `runs: { total, byStatus, lastRunAt, attention }` — where `attention` counts linked runs whose next step is a human action (`paused`, `waiting_approval`, or `budget_exceeded`), the same signal as `GET /api/runs/attention`. The board surfaces it as a badge, and linked runs also move the ticket across lanes as they progress (see Boards)."],[953,"List approval cards (`pending` or `resolved`)"],[917,"List runs (filter by `status`, `q`, `workflow`)"],[936,"List schedules; create cron/one-shot schedules (admin)"],[905,"List workflows (`?q=` searches)"],[898,"List workflows, preflight your input, start the run, then poll it:"],[1330,"Liveness/readiness probes."],[1301,"Local gates are `test`, `build`, and `diff-check` (`git diff --check`); `sandbox-smoke` only runs on a real Actions kernel, so its evidence is recorded by hand from a green CI run. Evidence is keyed to the full HEAD SHA in `data/release-evidence.json`, so a green gate can never be inherited across new commits, and `status` tells you the next action (run a gate, fix a failure, tag)."],[1200,"Location label (`vps` or `local`) used for run routing"],[812,"Machine intake: workflow endpoints"],[940,"Manage access tokens (admin)"],[549,"Management (admin only)"],[1204,"Max concurrent runs (default 1)"],[1016,"MCP"],[1213,"MCP"],[1309,"MCP"],[35,"MCP